The paper deals with the development of a framework for accurate and robust left ventricle quantification using convolutional neural networks and U-Net architecture. This work involves computer vision, machine learning, and artificial intelligence techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
